Patch Set 5:

Testing:  This code has been in dev-bhyve for several weeks and as such has been run by everyone that is developing bhyve as well as those that have been testing it.  Others and I have verified that iasl works for common use cases.

I have run builds of this code outside of dev-bhyve as well.  No unexpected acpi messages were observed from the kernel, and iasl seems to work the same as it does in dev-bhyve.  No problems were observed with acpidump or acpixtract.

There's a lot of usr/src/cmd/common code that is compiled by various programs - the addition of iasl requires a bunch more.  Each program sets its own CFLAGS, etc.  If the common code isn't suitable for a shared library, it's not suitable for a static library either.

This script can be used to resync from https://acpica.org/sites/acpica/files/acpica-unix2-20160527.tar.gz and result in a workspace that shows now changes according to 'git diff'.  I did not resync from the git repository because that introduces license changes in many (all?) files.
